story.title: Littlefield - Part 2
story.storyDescription: Sarah finds a dead body in the woods and uncovers a dark and deadly mystery.

messages.text: H, please be there.
Hey, everything okay?
No. Sarah didn’t come home last night.
She’s not answering texts and her phone goes straight to voicemail.
I don’t know what to do.
Just breathe. She’s probably drunk on someone’s floor right now.
Don’t talk about her like that.
She’s never this late...
And she always calls me if that’s the case so I can cover for her...
I’m sorry.  Who was she hanging out with last night?
I don’t know. I never know who the fuck she’s hanging out with.
Can we can talk to your Dad??
People need to be missing for a specific amount of time before the police can do anything
But he’s the chief. Can’t he make an exception??
Probably not, especially since he knows how your sister is.
I’m sorry, and exactly HOW is my sister??
Oh come on , she’s a girl…about town, to put it nicely
And like a 70-year-old woman who snoops on people through her blinds.
My sister is NOT like that.
Again, I’m sorry, just kinda stating the truth
Well it doesn’t help me!! What do I do!??!
Let me think….Does she keep a diary?
Yeah.
Go and see if she mentions anyone in her last few entries.
Maybe we can crosscheck the names on her Facebook friends list?
And find out more from there
Good idea. Going into her room now.
See anything??
Yep…So far I know she wants to murder me for blasting Beyonce in my room.
Who doesn’t like Beyonce!?
My sister…She mentions some guy named Wayne
Okay, I’ll look at your sis’s fbook profile for a Wayne.
You keep looking for anyone else
It seems like she’s been pretty depressed, which makes me even more worried.
What if she killed herself?!
I see a Wayne Jennings, but found something more informative
What!?
Jared just posted a pic of a party from last night
he tagged your sister in it
Our neighbor?? Does it say where?? Do you have his number??
Yeah, I’ll text him to see what he knows
Is he responding??
Yeah, hold on…
So he definitely saw her there last night.
Where is this place?
Right down Anglersville Rd. It’s an abandoned warehouse.
Can you ask him if she was around a guy named Wayne?
Yes, but they didn’t leave together.
Apparently, she hung around until about 2AM, then left to meet someone.
WHO!?
She wouldn’t say, but he offered her a ride.
She said she wanted to walk instead.
WALK!?  WHY DID HE LET HER DO THAT!?
I asked him if he knew anyone else who knows who she might’ve gone to meet...
he said no.
We have to go to this place, NOW!!!
But she could be anywhere
We have to start somewhere!!
And how are we going to get there?! Neither of us drive.
We can ride our bikes!
It’s ten miles away
So then what do we do??
Are either of your parents home??
No they went to Costco. They think she’s sleeping.
My Dad will flip when he finds out she left the house.
They’ll probably just be happy if she’s found safe.
you should tell them
Can we please just call your Dad? Please.
Maybe he can find her before they know.
I can call him to see what he can do, but that’s all I can promise you.
Wait…he just came in the door. I’ll ask him now
Thank you!!!
What’s he saying??
HELENA??
I don’t know if I should tell you
TELL ME WHAT!??
He said they found a bunch of bodies in the North Woods.
WAS ONE OF THEM SARAH??
I don’t know.
He said he hasn’t seen the coroners reports yet...
but that the bodies were pretty mangled
I’m going to throw up…
Don’t jump to conclusions yet. I told him your sister’s been missing.
He’s going to check right now…
Oh God, my parents got home.
What do I do???
Click below to see what happens next...
